ased","1337":"1337","Abt 1309":"about 1309","1313":"1313","1389":"1389","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Frampton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places so called, of which there are several in Gloucestershire, one in Dorset and one in Lincolnshire. Most take the name from the Frome river in south Gloucestershire (which is probably from a British word meaning ‘fair, brisk’) + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’. One near Tewkesbury was originally named in Old English as <i>Frēolingtūn</i> ‘settlement associated with <i>Frēola</i>’, a short form of any of various compound personal names with the first element <i>frēo</i> ‘free’. Frampton in Lincolnshire probably gets its name from an Old English byname <i>Frameca</i> (a derivative of <i>fram</i> ‘valiant’) + <i>tūn</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Frome","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places so called, such as Frome (Somerset), Frome Saint Quintin, Frome Vauchurch, Frome Whitfield in Stinsford, the lost <i>Frome Billet</i> in West Stafford (all Dorset), Bishops Frome, Canon Frome, Castle Frome, and Prior's Frome and Larport (formerly <i>Frome</i>) both in Mordiford (all Herefordshire). Or a topographic name from the rivers on which these places are located, or simply a name for someone living beside a river of this name, which is probably cognate with Welsh <i>ffraw</i> ‘fair, fine, brisk’. Compare   Frampton  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Frampton was born about 1309, in Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. John Frampton about 1329, in Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1309–Deceased":"umbes 1309–Surnud","1313–Female":"1313–Surnud","1330–1389":"1330–1389","1337–Male":"1337–Surnud","1309–Male":"1309–Surnud","1337":"1337","Abt 1309":"umbes 1309","1313":"1313","1389":"1389","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Moreton, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1309–Deceased":"noin 1309–Kuollut","1313–Female":"1313–Kuollut","1330–1389":"1330–1389","1337–Male":"1337–Kuollut","1309–Male":"1309–Kuollut","1337":"1337","Abt 1309":"noin 1309","1313":"1313","1389":"1389","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Moreton, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1309–Deceased":"environ 1309–Décédé","1313–Female":"1313–Décédée","1330–1389":"1330–1389","1337–Male":"1337–Décédé","1309–Male":"1309–Décédé","1337":"1337","Abt 1309":"environ 1309","1313":"1313","1389":"1389","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Moreton, Dorset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John Frampton est né environ 1309, à Moreton, Dorset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Mrs. John Frampton environ 1329, à Moreton, Dorset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1309–Deceased":"um 1309–Verstorben","1313–Female":"1313–Verstorben","1330–1389":"1330–1389","1337–Male":"1337–Verstorben","1309–Male":"1309–Verstorben","1337":"1337","Abt 1309":"um 1309","1313":"1313","1389":"1389","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"John Frampton wurde um 1309 in Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hat um 1329 in Moreton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom Mrs. John 